President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation declaring October 20-26, 2019, as National Character Counts Week. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of developing and demonstrating admirable qualities in order to maintain freedom and strengthen the nation. It highlights the role of parents, mentors, and educators in instilling values in young people, and encourages setting a good example for the next generation. The proclamation also mentions the First Lady's BE BEST initiative, which promotes kindness, compassion, and respect. It acknowledges the outstanding character of historical figures and ordinary Americans who demonstrate virtues such as selflessness, honor, and devotion to duty. The proclamation calls upon public officials, educators, parents, students, and all Americans to observe the week with appropriate ceremonies, activities, and programs.